When historians look back on 2017, they’ll see an era of dystopian excess wherein even the worst ideas are played out to fruition. Donald Trump is our president, Rob Schneider is on Twitter , and they’re remaking White Men Can’t Jump . Worst yet, this evening brought the very real possibility of a collaboration between indie stalwarts Car Seat Headrest and the one band that even Trump wouldn’t want playing his inauguration, Smash Mouth .
Suggestion: @smashmouth & @carseatheadrest split EP where each covers a song by the other. Please make it happen.
